e\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gns1665702606915.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gns1665702606915.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gns1665702606915.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gns1665702606915\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determine processing required when printing right-to-left fields.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gns1665702606915__topic_d142892e1_d142893e1_d142894e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gns1665702606915__p_d142895e1_d142896e1_d142897e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RTL_PRINTING</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <var class=\"keyword varname\">ProcessingCode</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gns1665702606915__section_kf1_dqy_kwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1242200e65\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Processing Codes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">Code </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">No processing (default) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">Mirroring of data in\n                        fields</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">2</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">Mirroring, plus character\n                        shaping</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">3</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17192e1_d17193e1_d17194e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">Mirroring, character shaping, plus\n                        ligation</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gns1665702606915__section_ewr_gqy_kwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1242200e135\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gns1665702606915__table_d17195e1_d17196e1_d17197e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Any application assignment file </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gns1665702606915__section_vfn_jqy_kwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1242200e182\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gns1665702606915__p_d142907e1_d142908e1_d142909e1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RTL_PRINTING</span> determines the\n            amount of processing that Uniface performs before printing right-to-left fields (for\n            example, in an Arabic or Hebrew application). You can select the level of processing to\n            be done depending on the capabilities of the printer being used. If the printer is able\n            to handle right-to-left printing completely, the setting is not needed.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvf1665702657960.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Types of Character Sets</a><p>The installable character sets can be either single-byte or double-byte. Single-byte character sets can be divided into left-to-right and right-to-left.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527935\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527935\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$RTL_PRINTING Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determine processing required when printing right-to-left fields. $RTL_PRINTING { = } ProcessingCode Arguments Table 1. Processing Codes Code Description 0 No processing (default) 1 Mirroring of data in fields 2 Mirroring, plus character shaping 3 Mirroring, character shaping, plus ligation Defaults Assignment file: Any application assignment file Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: 0 Description $RTL_PRINTING determines the amount of processing that Uniface performs before printing right-to-left fields (for example, in an Arabic or Hebrew application). You can select the level of processing to be done depending on the capabilities of the printer being used. If the printer is able to handle right-to-left printing completely, the setting is not needed. Related Links Types of Character Sets The installable character sets can be either single-byte or double-byte. Single-byte character sets can be divided into left-to-right and right-to-left. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}